'''Daily Nous''' is a [[website]] that provides information and news for and about the [[philosophy]] profession. It is maintained by [[Justin Weinberg]], associate professor of philosophy at the [[University of South Carolina]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.insidehighered.com/news/2014/11/20/marquette-u-grad-student-shes-being-targeted-after-ending-class-discussion-gay|title=Ethics Lesson|last=Flaherty|first=Colleen|date=20 November 2014|website=Inside Higher Ed|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|accessdate=4 October 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Philosophers on Brexit - Daily Nous - Research Database, The University of York|url=https://pure.york.ac.uk/portal/en/journals/philosophers-on-brexit--daily-nous(3946f234-1431-4085-baa4-2fe7f48823bd)/publications.html|website=pure.york.ac.uk|accessdate=16 October 2017|language=en}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last1=Bollag|first1=Sophia|title=Investigators find Prof. Laura Kipnis did not violate Title IX|url=https://dailynorthwestern.com/2015/06/06/campus/investigators-find-prof-laura-kipnis-not-violate-title-ix/|website=dailynorthwestern.com|language=en}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last1=Bollag|first1=Sophia|title=Student suing Northwestern under Title IX files new evidence|url=https://dailynorthwestern.com/2015/01/09/campus/student-suing-northwestern-under-title-ix-files-new-evidence/|website=dailynorthwestern.com|accessdate=16 October 2017}}</ref>
