'''The Florida Space Research Institute''' (FSRI) was a statewide center for space research which was established by [[Governor of Florida|Florida's governor]] and the [[Florida legislature]] in 1999. The institute was created in an effort to increase collaboration between the academic, government, and private organizations with regard to aerospace. FSRI is closely involved with [[NASA]]'s [[Centennial Challenges]] program, and signed a cooperative agreement with [[Kennedy Space Center]] in order to collaborate on the [[Advanced Learning Environment]] (ALE) initiative in 2001.<ref>{{Cite press|url=http://www.spaceref.com/news/viewpr.html?pid=4059|accessdate=February 5, 2010|title=Florida Space Research Institute Signs Technology Contract with NASA|date=March 8, 2001|publisher=[[SpaceRef.com]]}}</ref> FSRI also co-sponsored the [[NASA Spaceport Engineering Design Student Competition 2003]] (NASA Spaceport 2003) along with the [[Florida Space Grant Consortium ]](FSGC).<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.floridaspacegrant.org/fsgc_higher_education2.php?ID=18|accessdate=February 5, 2010|title=NASA Spaceport Student Competition - Florida Space Grant Consortium|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090713160202/http://www.floridaspacegrant.org/fsgc_higher_education2.php?ID=18|archivedate=July 13, 2009|df=}}</ref>
== Consolidation into Space Florida == With the [[Space Florida Act]],<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://law.onecle.com/florida/aviation/331.302.html |accessdate=February 5, 2010 |title=Florida Aviation Code Section 331.302 - Aviation And Aerospace Facilities And Commerce - Space Florida; creation; purpose. - Florida Attorney Resources - Florida Laws: |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20081011031339/http://law.onecle.com/florida/aviation/331.302.html |archivedate=October 11, 2008 |df= }}</ref> enacted in May 2006, the [[Florida Legislature]] consolidated FSRI and two other organizations in order to create [[Space Florida]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.spaceflorida.gov/history.php |title=History of Space Florida |publisher=Space Florida |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090105184840/http://www.spaceflorida.gov/history.php |archivedate=2009-01-05 |df= }}</ref>
